title: Grateful Dead Live at Fillmore East on 1970-07-12
lineage: all transfers and work performed in the 24 bit realm Weiss-Saracon for 16 BIT 44.1kHz; SBE Free, Flac Level 8 with TLH, Meta Data with Tag & Rename
taper: Mystery Reel of an unknown audience recording uncovered  and shared by LL member Cloverman, which he sent to Matt Smith for his great reel transfer work.  The handwriting on the reel case is thought to be Latvala's, no more is known.
description:
SET 1: Dire Wolf, The Rub, How Long Blues, Dark Hollow, Friend Of The Devil, Candyman, Katie Mae, She's Mine, Rosalie McFall, Tell It To Me, Wake Up Little Susie

SET 2: Easy Wind, Mama Tried, Attics Of My Life, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, It's A Man's World, Cold Rain & Snow, High Time, Cryptical Envelopement-> Drums-> The Other One-> Me & My Uncle-> The Other One-> Dancin' In The Streets, Turn On Your Love Light

reviews.review_text: This one had esacped my ears! Thanx Jamie, Matt, & GEMS.  Great acoustic set, incredible ending with an off the charts Dancing.  Might be the 1st How Long Blues I've heard.  Attics is a real beauty, especially for this time period.  The sound is a definite C but the show is much more than that.  I am playing Cold Rain and Attics on my radio show tomorrow night.  Peace.

my first show The first time I saw them. Brings back memories. The park we used to get our weed and acid from was Bliss park in Bklyn ny. Ireremember the girl dealing asking " are you going to see the dead tonite?". I'd heard of them but never heard them. Anyway I saw an ad in the paper that they were playing at the Fillmore so me and my friend Norman went down to get tickets. A friend from grammer school came up to us and said he needed money for a ticket and had a place near the front of the line if we would give him a buck he would get us tickets. Agreed! He got us 5th row. That night we went to bliss and got 2 tabs of strawberry flat acid , dropped it and by thevtime we got to the Fillmore we were pretty wasted. An usher took us to our seats ( which were occupied by others) and we sat down. Jerry was singing " don't murder me". I was on the end of the row when a guy came up withna water gun and said "open your mouth" and shot us both with I assume was more acid. I don't remember alot of that night except thinking of the wo4d ecstasy.  I remember easy wind I swear pig pen came out in a horse driven carriage. I remember pig pen asking for a harmonica and expected my friend Devi to give him one ( he had gotten a ticket and was in the back rows). I remember dancing in the streets and lovelight. Lovelight was burned in my mind. After the show a friend John Stevens who was in thebsame row center. Came up to me ( I was huddled in my seat and said ( next time you'll be dancing". We walked out and smoker a joint then went to union square park. The next day I had to go to my grandmother's funeral. I remember thinking she wasn't really dead but on a different plane of existence. A seminal experience!!!
